Inside ProofSettle
Once verified sports intelligence enters ProofSettle, it passes through a transparent engineering pipeline before any settlement is authorized.
Step 1 — Verified Sports Intelligence
ProofSettle continuously receives verified sports intelligence from TxLINE, including historical data, live match events, consensus intelligence and validated statistics.
↓
Step 2 — Standardized Machine Readable Schema
Incoming sports intelligence is transformed into a standardized machine-readable structure.
This enables every sporting event to be interpreted consistently by deterministic business rules regardless of its origin.
↓
Step 3 — Smart Contract Rule Evaluation
Transparent business rules evaluate the standardized sports intelligence.
Every condition required for prediction settlement is checked systematically.
Only fully satisfied rule sets continue through the workflow.
↓
Step 4 — Decision Intelligence
The rule evaluation engine transforms validated sporting events into a trusted operational decision.
Every decision remains deterministic, reproducible and explainable.
↓
Step 5 — Mathematically Verifiable Decision Artifact
Rather than immediately executing settlement, ProofSettle generates a mathematically verifiable Decision Artifact representing the complete operational decision.
This artifact preserves the exact state of the decision before settlement.
↓
Step 6 — Cryptographic Merkle Tree
Decision Artifacts are organized into a cryptographic Merkle Tree structure.
This creates tamper-evident integrity while enabling efficient verification of every operational decision.
↓
Step 7 — Settlement Authorization
Only after all validations successfully complete does ProofSettle authorize settlement.
↓
Step 8 — Trustless Solana Settlement
The authorized decision is executed immutably on Solana through deterministic smart contract settlement.
